{"parse":{"title":"Homer (Ezekiel)","pageid":41732518,"revid":820220655,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;width: 22em; line-height: 1.4em; text-align: left; float:;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic\">Homer</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Old Cabell Hall and Homer University of Virginia.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg/300px-Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg/450px-Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg/600px-Old_Cabell_Hall_and_Homer_University_of_Virginia.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1152\" data-file-height=\"864\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Artist</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Moses_Jacob_Ezekiel\" title=\"Moses Jacob Ezekiel\">Moses Jacob Ezekiel</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Year</th><td>\n1907</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Type</th><td class=\"category\">\nBronze</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Dimensions</th><td>\n170&#160;cm&#32;\u00d7&#160;90&#160;cm&#32;\u00d7&#160;140&#160;cm&#32;(67&#160;in&#32;\u00d7&#160;35&#160;in&#32;\u00d7&#160;55&#160;in)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Charlottesville\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Charlottesville\">Charlottesville</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\"><span style=\"display:none\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a></span></th><td>\n<span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Homer_(Ezekiel)&amp;params=38_2_00_N_78_30_27_W_type:landmark\"><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">38\u00b02\u203200\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">78\u00b030\u203227\u2033W</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">38.03333\u00b0N 78.50750\u00b0W</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">38.03333; -78.50750</span></span></span></a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Owner</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Virginia\" title=\"University of Virginia\">University of Virginia</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Blind Homer With His Student Guide</b></i> is a bronze sculpture by <a href=\"/wiki/Moses_Jacob_Ezekiel\" title=\"Moses Jacob Ezekiel\">Moses Jacob Ezekiel</a> in the likeness of the blind poet <a href=\"/wiki/Homer\" title=\"Homer\">Homer</a>, author of the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Iliad\" title=\"Iliad\">Iliad</a></i>, accompanied by a student guide. Ezekiel completed the statue in 1907 on a commission from <a href=\"/wiki/John_Woodruff_Simpson\" title=\"John Woodruff Simpson\">John Woodruff Simpson</a> as a gift for <a href=\"/wiki/Amherst_College\" title=\"Amherst College\">Amherst College</a>, his alma mater.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bruce_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bruce-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> For reasons unknown the gift was refused, and <a href=\"/wiki/Thomas_Nelson_Page\" title=\"Thomas Nelson Page\">Thomas Nelson Page</a>, a Virginia alumnus who was active in the UVA Alumni Association, stepped in to secure the gift of the statue to UVa instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cd-2000_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cd-2000-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Ezekiel completed the work in his Rome studio and donated a five foot tall black marble pedestal upon which the statue was originally installed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-collegetopics_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-collegetopics-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-alumni-bulletin_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-alumni-bulletin-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The statue is installed on <a href=\"/wiki/The_Lawn\" title=\"The Lawn\">The Lawn</a>, in the grass to the north of <a href=\"/wiki/The_Lawn\" title=\"The Lawn\">Old Cabell Hall</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Homer_(Ezekiel)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-bruce-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-bruce_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Philip_Alexander_Bruce\" title=\"Philip Alexander Bruce\">Bruce, Philip Alexander</a> (1921). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/historyuniversi05brucgoog#page/n334/mode/2up\"><i>History of the University of Virginia</i></a>. <b>V</b>. p.&#160;320.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+University+of+Virginia&amp;rft.pages=320&amp;rft.date=1921&amp;rft.aulast=Bruce&amp;rft.aufirst=Philip+Alexander&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Fhistoryuniversi05brucgoog%23page%2Fn334%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomer+%28Ezekiel%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-cd-2000-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-cd-2000_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Roberts, Josie (2000-04-07). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cavalierdaily.com/article/2000/04/homers-odyssey-brings-him-to-lawn/\">\"Homer's Odyssey brings him to Lawn\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Cavalier_Daily\" title=\"The Cavalier Daily\">The Cavalier Daily</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-01-24</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Cavalier+Daily&amp;rft.atitle=Homer%27s+Odyssey+brings+him+to+Lawn&amp;rft.date=2000-04-07&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.aufirst=Josie&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cavalierdaily.com%2Farticle%2F2000%2F04%2Fhomers-odyssey-brings-him-to-lawn%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomer+%28Ezekiel%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-collegetopics-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-collegetopics_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=RQ0tAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=3GkEAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=2202%2C3971605\">\"Bronzes of Homer and Jefferson\"</a>. <i>College Topics</i>. 1907-03-23. p.&#160;1<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-01-24</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Ak